{
  "texts": [
    "These challenges are closely linked to the inherent complexity of sensory systems and the interplay among biological, technical, and ethical factors.",
    "(1) Subjective Perception and Cultural Influences.",
    "Sensory perception varies significantly among individuals due to genetic predispositions, cultural traditions, and personal experiences.",
    "For instance, certain food aromas or flavors that evoke positive responses in one culture may be unappealing or even aversive in another (Taylor 2002; Reddy and van Dam 2020).",
    "Furthermore, genetic variations in taste receptors can lead to different sensitivities to bitter compounds, complicating the task of creating universal models."
  ]
}